  "title": "Motion of orbiting satellite - energy two points",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A satellite has speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v\"><math alttext=\"v\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>v</mi></math></span></span> when it is at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span>, which is located outside Earth’s atmosphere a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> from Earth’s center. The satellite then fires its thrusters and eventually reaches point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math></span></span>, a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"5 R\"><math alttext=\"5 R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>5</mn><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> from Earth’s center, where the satellite again has speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v\"><math alttext=\"v\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>v</mi></math></span></span>. The total mechanical energy of the satellite-Earth system is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub P\"><math alttext=\"E sub P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></msub></math></span></span> when the satellite is at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub Q\"><math alttext=\"E sub Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></msub></math></span></span> when the satellite is at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub Q\"><math alttext=\"E sub Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>Q</mtext></msub></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub P\"><math alttext=\"E sub P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>P</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, and provides a valid justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub Q equals E sub P\"><math alttext=\"E sub Q equals E sub P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>Q</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>P</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, because the thruster exerts a force equal in magnitude and opposite in direction to the gravitational force exerted by Earth.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub Q equals E sub P\"><math alttext=\"E sub Q equals E sub P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>Q</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>P</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, because the satellite has the same kinetic energy at both points.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub Q is greater than E sub P\"><math alttext=\"E sub Q is greater than E sub P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>Q</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>P</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, because the gravitational potential energy increases with increasing distance from Earth’s center.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub Q is greater than E sub P\"><math alttext=\"E sub Q is greater than E sub P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>Q</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>P</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, because the total mechanical energy of the system is proportional to the distance between the satellite and Earth’s center.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
